Usage: revamp [OPTIONS]... [arg1]... [arg2]
A utility to move file or folders from arg1 to arg2 without requiring to change the links and references.

-nd                          do not delete the destination file/folder
-f,                          do not prompt before overwriting
-i,                          prompt before overwrite (default)
-no,                         do not overwrite an existing file
If more than one of -i, -f, -no is specified, only the final option is accepted.
-t,                          move file/folder at arg1 into arg2(arg2 must be a directory).


-h                            display this help.
-version                      output version information
If no options are provided, the revamp command line is opened.
